	"documentnotes": {
		"note": [
			{
				"text": "\nAn update is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8.\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Important. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.\n    ",
				"title": "Topic",
				"type": "Summary",
				"ordinal": "1",
				"lang": "en"
			},
			{
				"text": "\nThis is a kernel live patch module which is automatically loaded by the RPM post-install script to modify the code of a running kernel.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* kernel: powerpc: KVM guest OS users can cause host OS memory corruption (CVE-2021-37576)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n    ",
				"title": "Details",
				"type": "General",
				"ordinal": "2",
				"lang": "en"
			},
			{
